	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>19th April 5624</date></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#8212;</p>
				<p rend="indent(1)">I only received yours of<lb/> <date>12th</date>&#44; this morning&#8212;it has been<lb/> detained fully four days.  Had I<lb/> received it earlier&#44; I should have <lb/>sent a reply at once asking you<lb/> to send <del>fr</del> the books.  As it is&#44;<lb/> their sale will be <sic>spoilt</sic> till<lb/> the fall holy days.  You can however<lb/> send them at once at the prices<lb/> named&#8212;and bound.  There may<lb/> perhaps be a call for a couple of<lb/> sets on <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; tho&#39; I doubt this.<lb/>  As I shall then not be able to sell<lb/> till the time mentioned&#44; I may make<lb/> you wait for your money till I<lb/> collect it in <placeName>New York</placeName> where it is<lb/> due me.  I have had to lose considerably<lb/> by sending books to <placeName>New York</placeName> when</p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways in the left margin">My kind regards to <persName>Miss <sic>Grats</sic></persName> when you see her. S. O. P.</p> 
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>bills were at par&#44; I foolishly<lb/> refrained from drawing&#44;<lb/> at the time&#44; <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">By the way&#44; will you please tell me<lb/> whether <persName>Cohen</persName> of the &#8220;Record&#8221; is in<lb/> your estimation likely to pay<lb/> an amount of about &#36;100 he owes<lb/> me for books&#8212;most of which<lb/> he ordered during the past year<lb/>&#8212;some were Catechisms for the<lb/> Sunday School <add>&#63;</add> in<lb/> <placeName>New York</placeName>.  Of course this is<lb/> entirely <add>Hebrew</add>.  Have you<lb/> found him prompt&#63;&#8212;for I<lb/> presume he has had books from you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I shall write to inform<lb/> <persName>Mr. Joseph</persName> what you write<lb/> about the Bibles.  They are<lb/> no doubt at his agents&#44; for</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>it was only yesterday &#40;<date>18th</date>&#41; we were<lb/> speaking about them&#44; as he happened<lb/> to be here on a visit.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">What you write about <persName>Mrs<lb/> Nadper</persName> surprises me very much&#8212;<lb/>for I had always been accustomed<lb/> to pay <persName>Mr J. H. Joseph</persName> my sum<lb/> I received for you.  I was fully<lb/> aware <persName>Mrs Nadper</persName> paid me&#8212;though<lb/> forget the sum &#38; date.  I think<lb/> I shall find I paid it to <persName>Mr Joseph</persName>&#44;<lb/> but shall look into it.  I must<lb/> wait till after <add>Hebrew</add> to write you<lb/> again&#44; for I have not an hours leisure<lb/> that I see before me.  I have just<lb/> been requested to give the annual<lb/> address at the Convocation of Mc<lb/> Gill University&#44; I cannot refuse</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>&#8212;it takes place on <date>third May</date>&#44;<lb/> I have examinations&#44; and<lb/> now every day Synagogue duties<lb/> that will occupy me for 9 days<lb/>&#8212;besides a review of a review<lb/> of <persName>Renau</persName> on the analogies of the<lb/> Semitic languages &#38; the <hi rend="underline">Iroquois</hi><lb/> &#38; <hi rend="underline">Algonquia</hi>&#33;  My answer is<lb/> to <persName>N. O.</persName> a priest of the seminary<lb/> here&#44; who writes anonymously<lb/>&#8212;and a fellow student of <persName>Renau</persName>.<lb/>  I write &#40;also anonymously&#41; at<lb/> the request of <persName>Dr Danhou<add>&#63;</add></persName> who is not<lb/> &#8220;up&#8221; in the Semitic languages&#8212;and the<lb/> part which he has already seen of<lb/> the manner I handle the priest has<lb/> given him not a little amusement.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">But I must close.  If you<lb/> could only see how I am writing in the<lb/> midst of scrubbing &#8220;preparing for <date>Pesach</date>&#8221;<lb/> you would say I must be a very determined<lb/> fellow. <add>Hebrew</add> Muchos <sic>annos</sic><lb/> y buenos.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways at the left side of the page">I will send you the continuation of the Biography after the Holy days<lb/> Please let me hear soon from you&#44; &#38; it seems well perhaps to send<lb/> the books soon&#44; on account of use &#38; rate of exchange.  Where gold was 90 in <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> a draft on <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> was worth 65 here.<lb/> i.e 35 to 40 discourse</p>
